ProphetBuy(uint256,address,address,uint2.details: This function includes a fee mechanism and supports fee-on-transfer tokens

params.amountOutMin: The minimum amount of output tokens to receive
params.deadline: The time by which the transaction must be confirmed
params.tokenAddress: The address of the output token

ProphetMaxBuy(uint256,address,address,ui.details: Executes a ProphetMaxBuy transaction, swapping Ether for the specified token.Refunds any unused Ether back to the sender in case of unsuccessful swaps.Handles multiple attempts to execute the ProphetBuy function in case of failure, with decreasing input Ether amounts.Updates the minimum Ether required for the specified token if the swap is successful.Emits a `tokenToEtherChanged` event on successful update.

params.amountOutMin: The minimum amount of the output token that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.deadline: The timestamp by which the transaction must be executed to prevent it from expiring.
params.to: The address that will receive the output tokens.
params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to be bought.

ProphetSell(uint256,uint256,address,uint.details: This function includes a fee mechanism and supports fee-on-transfer tokens

params.amountIn: The amount of input tokens to sell
params.amountOutMin: The minimum amount of ETH to receive
params.deadline: The time by which the transaction must be confirmed
params.tokenAddress: The address of the input token

ProphetSmartSell(uint256,uint256,address.details: This function includes a fee mechanism and uses internal swap functions

params.amountInMax: The maximum amount of input tokens to sell
params.amountOut: The amount of ETH to receive from the swap
params.deadline: The time by which the transaction must be confirmed
params.tokenAddress: The address of the token to sell

acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

getContractBalance().details: Gets the current balance of Ether held by the contract.

returns._0: The current Ether balance of the contract.

params.swapETH: Indicates whether the swap involves ETH -> tokenAddr
params.tokenAddr: The address of the other token

returns._0: path The swap path as an array of addresses

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

setMaxBuyEtherLimit(uint256).details: Sets the maximum buy ether limit.

params.newLimit: The new maximum buy ether limit to be set.

setTokenToEther(address,uint256).details: Sets the minimum Ether required to buy a specific token address.Emits a `tokenToEtherChanged` event on successful update.

params.value: The new minimum Ether required for the specified token.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

updateMaxBuyScale(uint256).details: Allows the owner to update the maxBuyScale variable.

updateMaxRetry(uint256).details: Allows the owner to update the maxRetry variable.

ProphetBuy(uint256,address,address,uint2.notice: Executes a buy operation with a fee, swapping ETH for tokens

ProphetMaxBuy(uint256,address,address,ui.notice: Use the ProphetMaxBuy only when buying the tokens which have max buy limit per transactionEnsure that the transaction is executed before the specified deadline.

ProphetSell(uint256,uint256,address,uint.notice: Executes a sell operation with a fee, swapping tokens for ETH and supporting fee-on-transfer tokens

ProphetSmartSell(uint256,uint256,address.notice: Executes a smart sell operation with a fee, swapping tokens for ETH

getPathForTokenToToken(bool,address).notice: Helper function to get the swap path for token to token or ETH to token swaps

setTokenToEther(address,uint256).notice: Only the owner can call this function.

withdrawETH().notice: Allows the contract owner to withdraw ETH from the contract
